					</div>
				</div>
				<div id="27safe">
					<div class="station">Sassnitz Ferry terminal</div>
					<div class="desc">
						Sassnitz Faehrhafen station sits directly within the Mukran Port
						complex on the island of Ruegen, providing seamless rail‑to‑ferry
						connections to Rønne (Bornholm) and Trelleborg (Sweden). It is the
						western terminus of the seasonal RE27 service, operated by
						Hanseatische Eisenbahn, which runs primarily on Saturdays and
						Sundays between May and October, offering one or two trains per
						direction per day timed to ferry departures and arrivals
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
